      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i know i can call someone but that feels so performative. like, how is a stranger on a phone gonna make the fact that i'm fundamentally irrelevant any less true? it's just... it's a quiet realization. if i just drifted away, the world wouldn't even flinch. it's almost peaceful to think about how little of an impact i actually have. like it wouldn't even be a tragedy, just a tiny footnote that nobody reads.",
